        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Sensitivity:
We request a sensitivty of 4 mJy per beam to ensure we detect the line emission from the ~ 305 GHz line transitions of CH3OH at the requested spatial resolution. This sensitivity is determined by scaling our model predictions by the source distance, disk size, and inclination.  Scaling our models sugests a peak flux per beam of ~ 40 mJy for V 4046 Sgr, therefore a sensitivity of 4 mJy will give a S/N ~ 10.  The requested spectral resolution (~ 0.2 km/s, smoothed) is sufficient to resolve the line emission since we expect a linewidth of ~ 4 km/s based on existing observations. 

Imaging:
We have sufficient time on source (~ 60 mins) to achieve good uv-coverage for imaging.  

Correlator setup:
We wish to observe mutiple rotational transitions of methanol in Band 7 at 304, 305, 307, and 318 GHz.  We request all lines because the range of energies of the different upper energy levels (22, 28, 38, and 98 K) will allow us to characterise the temperature of the emitting gas.  Our spectral setup also allows us to observe the ground-state transition of ortho-D2O.  All lines can be observed simultaneously in a single correlator tuning and we require only 1/4 of the total baseband per line.   

We have no special requirements regarding calibration and bandpass accuracy nor any scheduling or time constraints.  The data rate is within the requested limit.  

  

</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
